    <item>
      <title>Rethinking the Way You Think</title>
      <link>https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/lesson/02-lesson/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/lesson/02-lesson/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;script src=&#34;https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/rmarkdown-libs/header-attrs/header-attrs.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;div id=&#34;TOC&#34;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#responses&#34;&gt;Responses&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#evaluation-definitions&#34;&gt;Evaluation Definitions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#considering-program-evaluation&#34;&gt;Considering Program Evaluation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div id=&#34;responses&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responses&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Read through posts on &lt;a href=&#34;https://2021edp617.slack.com/archives/C01KL7W6H6V&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;#pictures-of-evaluation&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and comment on at least one posting using the &lt;a href=&#34;https://slack.com/help/articles/115000769927-Use-threads-to-organize-discussions-&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Reply in thread&lt;/a&gt; option as pictured below: &lt;img src=&#34;https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/img/lesson/slack_pop_menu.png&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;evaluation-definitions&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Evaluation Definitions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look through the &lt;a href=&#34;https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/handouts/Evaluation%20Definitions.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;evaluation definitions&lt;/a&gt; document.
Think about which of those definitions fits best with your own view of evaluation, or if there are components of your view that are not addressed by any of those definitions. Then write a single post on &lt;a href=&#34;https://2021edp617.slack.com/archives/C01L18T7NR2&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;#evaluation-definitions&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; describing your view of evaluation and how it connects with any or all (or none) of the definitions described.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;considering-program-evaluation&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Considering Program Evaluation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please take and complete the survey &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Considering Program Evaluation&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; that has been sent to your e-mail. While I ask that you please fill it out truthfully, please note there is no right or wrong answer. This is just an initial assessment of what you may or may not know or be aware of within the field of evaluation and provides me with an initial benchmark for the class. If you did not receive an invite, please let me know as soon as possible!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
