&lt;div id=&#34;respond-to-posts&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Respond to Posts&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please create &lt;strong&gt;one response&lt;/strong&gt; for the post below on Slack.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://2021edp617.slack.com/archives/C01L18T7NR2&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;#evaluation-definitions&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;note-about-the-responding-to-posts&#34; class=&#34;section level3&#34;&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Note about the responding to posts&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your responses to postings should follow the same basic criteria outlined in the original post. Remember to use the &lt;code&gt;Reply in thread&lt;/code&gt; option when replying! If you need a reminder on how to do this, please click &lt;a href=&#34;https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/lesson/02-lesson/#responses&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;evaluation-approaches&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Evaluation Approaches&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look through the CDC’s &lt;a href=&#34;https://edp617.theoreticalphysed.com/handouts/Types%20of%20Evaluation.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Types of Evaluations&lt;/a&gt; document to get yourself familiarized with various approaches to conducting evaluations. It is important to note that &lt;em&gt;summative evaluations&lt;/em&gt; are not listed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&#34;creating-evaluation-teams&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Creating Evaluation Teams&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finalize your evaluation teams that must consist of three to four members. Then talk among yourselves to figure out three possible weekly meetings times/days that you can get together to discuss materials about the course and the eventual evaluation. To begin, I will join you on a biweekly basis to discuss items and to answer any questions you may have. If the team appears to be on track as we progress, I will reduce my participation unless needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please fill out the necessary columns in the csv file addressing&lt;/p&gt;
